comment:
File: qg.order100.col
Source: Carla Gomes (gomes@cs.cornell.edu)
Description: This is an instance of the Quasigroup or Latin Square Problem
(order 100).
The problem corresponds to assigning colors to the 100 x 100 cells
of an empty matrix such there are no repetitions of colors
in each row/column of the matrix.
Graph Structure: The graph has 10000 nodes and 990000 edges.
Num. colors (optimal): 100

FILE: abb313GPIA.col
SOURCE: Shahadat Hossain and Trond Steihaug
DESCRIPTION: Graph obtained from a matrix partitioning problem
in the segmented columns approach to determine
sparse Jacobian matrices.
Given a matrix A determine G_\Pi(A) where \Pi is a row
partition of A. Matrix A for this graph is ABB313
from SMTAPE package of Harwell-Boeing test matrix collection.
